  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Education and Livelihoods for refugees in Galkayo, Somalia.</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The overall objective of this intervention is to respond to the needs of Refugees in Galkayo by building framework that ensures access to formal education response. Through this programme, UNHCR and Relief International ensure that all refugee children of school age in Galkayo district have access to basic (from 1st grade to 8th grade) and secondary education.  Refugee children in Galkayo are enrolled in national schools in Galkayo just like the host Somali children. Relief International provides counselling to families of school going children with an observed inconsistent attendance trend and provides support in identifying families of school going children who cannot provide support to their children because of social circumstances (physical, protection).</narrative>
  </description>
